.TH "setup_direct_dde" 9 "setup_direct_dde" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
setup_direct_dde \- Setup single DDE from buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" setup_direct_dde
.BI "(struct data_descriptor_entry *dde "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pa "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dde" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "pa" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "len" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The DDE is setup with the buffer and length.  The buffer must be properly
aligned.  The used length is returned.
.SH "RETURN"
N    Successfully set up DDE with N bytes
